lc command.
lc is tiny shell script that automaticay ls when cd.

Install 
Put file "lc" into $Home/bin (or directory what will be loaded automaticay)
and execute

$ alias lc=". lc"
Because "cd" in shellscript has no effects in parent process.
You should put "alias lc=". lc" into the file what will be loaded automaticay.

Usage,

$ lc directory

You can't use ls options.
But you can define it in file "lc".
